    <h1>Kyoto: A Journey through Tradition and Beauty</h1>
    <img src="https://example.com/kyoto.jpg" alt="Kyoto Landscape">

    <p>Kyoto, once the capital of Japan, is a city that blends ancient traditions with modern elegance. Known for its stunning temples, beautiful gardens, and historic wooden houses, Kyoto is a destination that offers a glimpse into Japan's rich cultural heritage. For more information about Kyoto, visit the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kyoto">Wikipedia page</a>.</p>

    <h2>Must-Visit Attractions</h2>
    <p>When visiting Kyoto, there are several attractions that should not be missed. These sites offer a mix of natural beauty and historical significance:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Kinkaku-ji (Golden Pavilion)</strong> - A Zen Buddhist temple covered in gold leaf.</li>
        <li><strong>Fushimi Inari Shrine</strong> - Famous for its thousands of vermilion torii gates.</li>
        <li><strong>Arashiyama Bamboo Grove</strong> - A serene and picturesque bamboo forest.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Delicious Kyoto Cuisine</h2>
    <p>Kyoto is also renowned for its unique and exquisite cuisine. Here are some dishes you must try:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Kaiseki</strong> - A traditional multi-course meal.</li>
        <li><strong>Yudofu</strong> - A hot tofu dish often enjoyed in winter.</li>
        <li><strong>Matcha</strong> - High-quality powdered green tea used in tea ceremonies.</li>
    </ol>

